law.text:
With respect to KRS 234.310 to 234.440, it is unlawful for any person to:
Fail to pay the taxes due;
Fail, neglect or refuse to make and file any statement required in the manner or within the time required;
Make any false statement or conceal any material fact in any record, report or affidavit;
Conduct any activities requiring a license without a license or after a license has been surrendered, canceled or revoked;
Assign or attempt to assign a license to act as a liquefied petroleum gas motor fuel dealer;
Violate any other provisions.
